Q. They were found at their own house, were they not? - A. No;
Henry Smith
was, the other two were found at Bow-street.

Q. Did you see any windows broke? - A. Yes, I saw Macdonald break three squares of glass;
John Wobbler
came to light his pipe at the table that Macdonald sat at; Macdonald took up the candle, and would not let him light his pipe; there was a scussle between them, and the candle went out; I saw his elbow go through one square of glass, and then they scussled to the other side of the tap-room, and broke two more.
